                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS00000">Gabra ʾIyasus</persName>Gabra ʾIyasus (<locus target="6va">6va</locus>, ls. 6-7).<date>Late 18th – early 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; chapter numbers and the word mǝˤǝraf; incipits of Gospel chapters and of minor texts (two initial lines); some of the marginal notes repeating chapter titles or indicating the liturgical occasions on which given sections should be read; name of the donor; parts of the Canon tables; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic numbers indicating the “tituli”.&#xD;
&#xD;
Incipits of Text I and of each of the four Gospels are written alternately in red and black lines (s. fols. 1r, 14r, 68r, 103r, 160r).</seg>
